title: GF(2)
summary: GF(2) (also denoted F 2 {\displaystyle \mathbb {F} _{2}} , Z/2Z or Z / 2 Z {\displaystyle \mathbb {Z} /2\mathbb {Z} } ) is the finite field of two elements (GF is the initialism of Galois field, another name for finite fields). Notations Z2 and Z 2 {\displaystyle \mathbb {Z} _{2}} may be encountered although they can be confused with the notation of 2-adic integers.
